            </span>
            <span class="ho-qs-arrow">›</span>
          </summary>
          <div class="ho-qs-body">
            <p>The foundation is built in lifts of compacted aggregate — typically 2 to 4 inches at a time — to the standard your project demands. Patios get at least 4 inches; driveways get 8 inches; pool decks and parking get more. Every lift is compacted with the right equipment so the base reaches 98% Standard Proctor density before we move on.</p>
            <p>Drainage is engineered in at this phase, not bolted on later. Surfaces are sloped a minimum of 2% away from structures, and where the project calls for it, perforated pipe and free-draining backfill carry water out before it can pool, freeze, or heave.</p>
          </div>
        </details>
        <details class="ho-qs-card">
          <summary class="ho-qs-summary">
            <span class="ho-qs-num">03</span>
