          </summary>
          <div class="ho-qs-body">
            <p>Concrete pavers go down on a precisely screeded one-inch bedding-sand layer, with edge restraints staked into the compacted base. Joints get tight tolerances (1/16 to 3/16 inch) and proper polymeric jointing sand to lock everything together and resist weed and insect intrusion.</p>
            <p>Porcelain is a different beast — slabs are heavier, more brittle, and require pre-compacted bedding sand and 4mm plastic spacers between every unit. Porcelain is never compacted with a plate compactor after install (a common mistake that breaks slabs); we hand-set, level, and verify alignment instead.</p>
          </div>
        </details>
        <details class="ho-qs-card">
          <summary class="ho-qs-summary">
            <span class="ho-qs-num">04</span>
            <span class="ho-qs-title-wrap">
