          </summary>
          <div class="ho-qs-body">
            <p>Retaining walls are engineered, not stacked. We start with a leveling pad of compacted aggregate, lay the first course slightly below grade for stability, and build up using running-bond patterns with proper backfill drainage and (where required) geosynthetic reinforcement layers based on soil type and wall height.</p>
            <p>Fire features and seat walls get the same care — proper bases, weather-resistant adhesives where they belong, gas lines run by licensed plumbers when applicable, and finish caps mortared in to last.</p>
          </div>
        </details>
        <details class="ho-qs-card">
          <summary class="ho-qs-summary">
            <span class="ho-qs-num">05</span>
            <span class="ho-qs-title-wrap">
              <span class="ho-qs-title">Finishing &amp; warranty</span>
