            <p>The last day is when most homeowners notice everything coming together. Polymeric jointing sand goes in, gets activated with water, and locks every joint. Where the design calls for sealing, we use the right sealer for the surface — penetrating for natural stone, joint-stabilizing for concrete pavers, none for some porcelain — and apply only after the install has fully cured.</p>
            <p>Belgard's transferable lifetime limited warranty covers the materials, and we stand behind the workmanship. Adherence to ICPI (Interlocking Concrete Paver Institute) standards isn't optional for us — it's how we keep that warranty intact and how we sleep at night.</p>
            <a href="https://cdn.prod.website-files.com/67c10dbe66a9f7b9cf3c6e47/68d2db027d1d1b4ad1543f05_Bayside%20Pavers%20Presentation%20(1)_compressed%20(1).pdf" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="ho-qs-warranty-cta">📄 View full warranty PDF →</a>
